Key Pain Points 
•	Fragmented Information: Data is scattered across multiple platforms, creating inefficiencies. 
•	Cross-Checking Delays: Sales staff need to verify details through various sources, slowing down response times. 
•	Inconsistent Data: Conflicting information from different systems leads to confusion and errors. 
•	Outdated Updates: Lack of real-time availability and pricing data causes miscommunication with clients. 
•	Dependency on Colleagues: New or less experienced sales staff rely heavily on colleagues for up-to-date, accurate information. 
•	Cognitive Overload: Sales executives are expected to remember too much without sufficient support tools. 
•	Insufficient Training: Onboarding is unstructured, with limited resources for new hires to learn. 
•	Lack of Visual Tools: No interactive maps or clear visual aids make it harder to convey project details to clients. 
•	Unreliable Systems: Internal digital tools are often slow or fail to load, especially during high-traffic periods. 
•	Repetitive Work: Sales executives frequently answer the same client questions without automation or standardized responses. 
•	Communication Gaps: Poor coordination between departments ( sales, legal, site offices) causes delays and misinformation. 
•	Version Control Issues: Multiple versions of documents make it difficult to know which ones are current or accurate. 
•	Client Interaction Pressure: Sales staff feel the pressure to respond instantly, leading to mistakes or hesitation. 
•	Experience Breakdown: Delays and hesitation during client interactions lead to a poor experience and reduced confidence. 

